#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:5
msgid "Contributing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:7
msgid ""
"Anyone can contribute to Emscripten — if you find it useful and want to help "
"improve the project, follow the suggestions below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:10
msgid ""
"Feel free to file :ref:`bug reports <bug-reports>`, :ref:`join the "
"discussion <contact>` and share your own ideas with the community!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:15
msgid "Getting started"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:17
msgid ""
"A good starting point is to work on the `open issues on GitHub <https://"
"github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten/issues?state=open>`_. Many issues can "
"be resolved without an in-depth knowledge of compiler internals, and this is "
"a great way to learn more about the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:22
msgid ""
"We really appreciate your help. Every existing issue closed means more time "
"for the core contributors to work on new features, optimizations and other "
"enhancements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:26
msgid ""
"In addition to improving the toolchain, you can also :ref:`review and update "
"this documentation <about-this-site-contributing>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:31
msgid "Next steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:33
msgid ""
"As a new contributor you should read the :ref:`Developer's-Guide`. You may "
"also need to :ref:`install Emscripten from source <installing-from-source>` "
"and become familiar with :ref:`Debugging` and :ref:`Building-Projects`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/contributing/contributing.rst:37
msgid ""
"Please :ref:`get in touch with the community <contact>` to share your ideas "
"and work out where you can make the most difference."
msgstr ""
